note: Rubber stamped date 21 June 1898 with notation in pencil, "Barrys 80" (f. 94v); numerous notations in ink on the flyleaves.

msContents.summary: Simply written copy with marginalia. The final folio has a large tear across the center, where part of the colophon is located, repaired with blank paper.

supportDesc.extent: 96 foliated leaves : 206 x 140 (143 x 79) mm, bound to 205 x 145 x 17 mm

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in nastaʻlīq in black ink; pointed.

decoNote: Rubrications in red; textblock ruled in red.

binding.p: Soft brown leather with blind stamped central mandorla and blind ruling (Type III); green paper doublure.

origin.p: Copy completed in Dhū al-Ḥijjah 1036 AH (1627 CE) (f. 94r).

history.provenance: Formerly owned by a Musṭafā ʻAlī (three partially legible stamps, f. 95v).
